These bantering verses are addressed to Horace's friend Iccius, a philosophie dilettante, who suddenly showed an interest in the prepara— tions for a campaign against Arabia Felix, under the direction of Aelius Gallus. The attempt terminated unsuecessfully in 24 B.C. The date of composition therefore may be approximately fixed as 26 B.C. or early 25 B.C'.
